    "summary": "Match Group posted first-quarter revenue above estimates on Tuesday, driven by the solid performance of dating app Hinge and early signs that a ‌turnaround at Tinder is gaining traction amid a broad push for AI-led transformation.  Shares ‌of the company rose about 5% in extended trading.  Match, which owns Tinder, Hinge, OkCupid and Plenty of Fish, has ​been retooling its products around AI-powered features aimed at improving match quality and reducing \"swipe fatigue,\" a sense of burnout among users overwhelmed by endless profiles and underwhelming connections.",
